```

âœ”ï¸ Output means Snort installed successfully

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 4: Edit Snort Configuration

```bash
sudo nano /etc/snort/snort.conf
```

Find:

```conf
ipvar HOME_NET any
```

Replace with:

```conf
ipvar HOME_NET 192.168.1.0/24
```

Save â†’ `CTRL+O` â†’ Enter â†’ `CTRL+X`

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 5: Create Snort Rule (PING Detect)

```bash
sudo nano /etc/snort/rules/local.rules
```

Paste:

```conf
alert icmp any any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ICMP PING DETECTED"; sid:1000001; rev:1;)
```

Save & Exit

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 6: Test Snort Configuration

```bash
sudo snort -T -c /etc/snort/snort.conf
```

âœ”ï¸ Expected:

```
Snort successfully validated the configuration!
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 7: Run Snort (IDS Mode)

```bash
sudo snort -A console -q -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0
```

â¡ï¸ Snort is now listening

